message.content: We refer to Wikipedia articles on medicine for help. The dysmorphic facial features and genetic analysis showing a deletion of the long arm of chromosome 7 suggest Williams syndrome. Supravalvular aortic stenosis is a commonly associated cardiovascular complication in patients with Williams syndrome. Hand flapping movements are more commonly associated with autism spectrum disorders, Brushfield spots on the iris with Down syndrome, and testicular enlargement with precocious puberty.
